From 896a3afe53b76d1493c765369f2437fb84b91386 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Miroslav Zagorac <mzagorac@haproxy.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 21:17:35 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] [EXPORTERS] Add MaybeSpawnBackgroundThread() to OTLP File
 exporters

The file system backend's background flush thread is started lazily on the
first Export() call via the private SpawnBackgroundWorkThread() method.

Added a virtual MaybeSpawnBackgroundThread() method to the
OtlpFileAppender interface (default no-op) and overrode it in
OtlpFileSystemBackend to call SpawnBackgroundWorkThread() directly.
Exposed the method through OtlpFileClient and all three OTLP File exporter
classes (traces, metrics, logs) so callers can pre-spawn the flush thread
immediately after construction.  The ostream backend inherits the default
no-op since it has no background thread.
